-- Thailand Stock Movers: Bangchak Petroleum, PTT Exploration, PTT
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-07-09T09:48:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/thailand-stock-movers-bangchak-petroleum-ptt-exploration-ptt.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  fell 1.1 percent to 1,186.95, the largest
decrease since June 21.  Oil companies:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s largest energy
company, dropped 2.1 percent to 327 baht, the steepest decline
since June 22.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the
country’s only publicly traded oil explorer, lost 2.3 percent to
173 baht.  Crude oil slid 3.2 percent on the New York Mercantile
Exchange on July 6, the biggest decline since June 21.  Bangchak Petroleum Pcl (BCP)  , a state-controlled oil
refiner, fell for a fourth day, losing 3.2 percent to 21.40
baht. The stock closed at the lowest level since Feb. 14. The
company may shut its crude-processing unit for three months for
maintenance after a fire, it said on July 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
